<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis undulata" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="undulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis undulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. subpruinosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="subpruinosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. subpruinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Murrill) R.H. Petersen. 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis subpruinosa" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="subpruinosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis subpruinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has differences in having small central papilla on pileus, fewer lamellulae (3-4 series), vivid colored lamellae, thicker basidiospores (4.5-5.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
wide), larger basidia (30-36 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7.5-8.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) and cheilocystidia (25-80 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-16 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
), thick-walled trama hyphae (0.5-1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
), caulocystidia with a wider size range, and a habit of growing solitary on rotten twigs or logs (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" author="Desjardin, DE" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="166 - 176" refId="B10" refString="Desjardin, DE, Halling, RE, Hemmes, DE, 1999. Agaricales of the Hawaiian Islands. 5. The genera Rhodocollybia and Gymnopus. Mycologia 91 (1): 166 - 176, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" title="Agaricales of the Hawaiian Islands. 5. The genera Rhodocollybia and Gymnopus." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" volume="91" year="1999">Desjardin et al. 1999</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis undulata" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="undulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis undulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is phylogenetically close to 
<taxonomicName genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. villosipes" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="villosipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. villosipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but 
<taxonomicName genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. villosipes" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="villosipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. villosipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated by having fewer lamelluale (2-3 series), vivid colored lamellae, thicker stipe (1.5-4.0 mm), slightly thicker basidiospores (3.5-4.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
wide), and basidia (25-34 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6.5-7.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Desjardin, DE" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="141 - 148" refId="B9" refString="Desjardin, DE, Halling, RE, Perry, BA, 1997. Gymnopus villosipes -a common collybioid agaric from California. Mycotaxon 64: 141 - 148" title="Gymnopus villosipes - a common collybioid agaric from California." volume="64" year="1997">Desjardin et al. 1997</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
